cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper deals with the analysis of social media content and its availability on the live web or in public web archives. The most relevant sub-category for this paper is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with the preservation and access to digital information. The paper also involves the use of information retrieval techniques to analyze the availability of social media content, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of social media on events, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the analysis of web archiving, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
